isDerivedFrom

private boolean isDerivedFrom(HibernateUtil.Operation operation,
                              java.util.List<CategoryType> checkedCategoryTypes,
                              CategoryType categoryType,
                              CategoryType from)
                       throws ServiceException
Checks if category type derives from indicated category type.

Note that this method keep track of previously checked categories types to avoid an infinite recursivity.

This case can occur if there is corrupted data within DB and then this method will break recursivity returning false.

Parameters:
operation - Operation
checkedCategoryTypes - Category types already checked
categoryType - Category type to check
from - Category type from we check if category type derives
Returns:
true if category type derives from indicated category type, false otherwise (or in case of corrupted data)
Throws:
ServiceException
